node.text:
-
When I train clients it’s not just their shot that I study. I watch their whole playing style, who they’re on the court with, and the role they play on their team. This helps me give more custom, complete training from how to set up their shot to actual muscle memory and how they can add the most value on the floor as a shooter. I coach every athlete differently to get the best out of them. Excited to start with the new players this summer.🎯
-
🎥 : @lethalshooter___ #WNBA #NBA #LethalShooter

-
🎥: @lethalshooter___ #NBA #LethalShooter

node.text:
Are you willing to do the same drill for 2hrs straight to master your gift?? Sometimes the difference between making it in the NBA and not is attention to detail. Pro athletes focus on the little things and it makes a big difference. They’re willing to learn and soak up all the feedback given to them in order to make the most detailed changes to their shot. If you really want to be successful, take your training seriously and stay locked in mentally during your sessions🎯. @greenranger14 #NBA #LethalShooter
-
🎥: @lethalshooter___

node.text: Growing up I never imagined getting in front of a camera - if anything it would be playing basketball in a televised game. But here I am, getting opportunities to shoot content with some of my favorite brands to share with the world. I’ve had to learn a lot to be ready for opportunities like these, but it just shows you can do anything if you work towards it. Never doubt God’s plan for your life and always trust the journey - even when it takes you unexpected places. Dream big always and be prepared for every opportunity that comes your way.🏀 -Stay locked in @jumpman23 #TeamNike #NBA #LethalShooter

node.text: As an athlete and coach it’s incredible to me to learn about how and why the sneakers we wear on the court are designed. Every detail helps maximize our performance and safety.  I appreciate Jordan Brand for allowing me to go Behind the Design for the AJ36 with designer, Tate. I’m blessed to be a part of a brand that continues to innovate to make us all better, faster, and stronger on the court. @jumpman23 #NBA #LethalShooter

node.text:
Always good to be back in the gym with my guys! Danny Green is truly committed to The Art of Shooting and every time we train we pick up where we left off. In EVERY category his shooting percentages IMPROVED last season. Leading the NBA in corner 3’s made. While doing so he took the most 3’s of his career in a season adding +4% to his percentage. Blessing to help others refine their games. -Stay locked in!🎯
-
🎥: @lethalshooter___ #NBA #LethalShooter
